description:
&lt;p&gt;NHS Wales Shared Services Partnership (NWSSP) is looking to recruit a Project Manager to support the growing development of the NWSSP PMO. The NWSSP PMO leads the implementation of a number of projects that support service improvement inline with IMTP (integrated medium term plans) strategic objectives and other key business requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Project Manager will be expected to have a sound understanding of NHS Wales and the relationship NWSSP has with Healthboards and Trusts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder must possess excellent communication and stakeholder management skills, which will help ensure policies processes and methodologies are developed and adopted across the organisation and wider boundaries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder must also be determined and passionate project manager focused on delivering projects and programmes to the highest standard, following already in use methods and clearly focused on benefits and successful business change.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to join a growing team and help play an active role it continued success for NWSSP, projects will vary between business change and I.T related projects offering excellent development opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh applicants are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date -&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ian Rose&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Head of PMO&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ian.rose@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
